The paper proposes a framework for formal developments using the COQ proof assistant to prove various properties of robot networks. The focus of the paper is on impossibility proofs for convergence of mobile robots with Byzantine failures. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Robotics (cs.RO), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
